---
title: Smoky Romesco New York Strip Steak with Asparagus and Toasted Couscous
description: Romesco sauce is one of Spain’s many great culinary gifts to the world. It features two distinctly Spanish flavors—sherry vinegar and smoked paprika—yet it’s versatile and pairs well with most meats and veggies. Here, its bright acidity is used to cut the richness of New York strip steak. On the side, charred asparagus and herbed couscous complete the breezy Mediterranean theme.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/15-11-c051ae11.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/15-11-70febe18.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 750 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 47 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 85 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/smoky-romesco-new-york-strip-steak-58af248ec9fd081c6d640113
time required: 45 minutes
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Trim and
discard woody bottoms from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.
Finely chop @parsley{¼%ounce}. Finely chop @almonds{1%ounce}. Cut ¼ of
@grape tomatoes{8%ounce} into quarters. Toss remaining whole tomatoes on a
foil-lined #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch
of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Broil (or roast) whole tomatoes until very soft and lightly charred, about
~{10%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #small pot{} over
medium heat. Add @Israeli couscous{½%cup} and cook, tossing, until toasted,
about ~{2%minutes}. Add half the garlic and cook until fragrant, about
~{1%minute}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add 1 cup water to pot and bring to a boil. Lower heat, reduce to a simmer, and
cover. Cook until tender, ~{8-10%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in tomato
quarters and half the parsley. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Once whole
tomatoes are done broiling, transfer to a #small bowl{} and let cool.

Mash tomatoes in bowl with a fork until smooth. Stir in almonds, remaining
parsley, remaining garlic, @smoked paprika{¼%tsp}, and
@red wine vinegar{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Adjust to taste with
more sherry vinegar, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper.

> We sent more paprika and vinegar than you will need. Save ¼ tsp smoked paprika
> for seasoning steak.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Pat @New York strip steak{10%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then season
all over with salt, pepper, and roasted smoked paprika. Add to pan and cook to
desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let rest.
Meanwhile, add asparagus to pan along with another drizzle of oil. Cook, tossing,
until lightly charred, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and add @butter{1%tbsp}. Toss to melt butter and coat
asparagus. Slice steak against the grain. Divide couscous, asparagus, and steak
between plates. Top with sauce and drizzle with any juices released by steak.